@{b}AmIRC 3.5 Guide - Table Of Content@{ub}
**********************************

Welcome to @{i}AmIRC@{ui}, the AmigaOS IRC client (Version 3.5).

Thank you for reading this manual as it will help you make the most out
of AmIRC and IRC in general. It will also prevent you from making a
fool of yourself by asking silly question during your first IRC
sessions.

Please don't forget to also read the @{i}Readme@{ui} file included in the
distribution archive as this will contain any last minute info that
might be important to you!

To help you find what you want in this manual we've provided you with
the following table of content. Feel free to jump directly to the
chapter of your choice or you can also just browse through them.



- Introduction -

 @{" About AmIRC " Link "About AmIRC"}       What is this program all about?
 @{" What's new? " Link "What's new?"}       List of all recently added features.
 @{" Features " Link "Features"}          Features of AmIRC.
 @{" Requirements " Link "Requirements"}      What is needed to use AmIRC?
 @{" Copyright " Link "Copyright"}         Copyrights, author info and more.
 @{" Registration " Link "Registration"}      Registering your copy.
 @{" Installation " Link "Installation"}      How to install AmIRC.
 @{" Connecting " Link "Connecting"}        Let's have a (first) go.
 @{" Operation " Link "Operation"}         Operation at a glance.

- Reference Section -

 @{" IRC Terms " Link "IRC Terms"}         Specific IRC vocabulary.
 @{" Menus " Link "Menus"}             What's on the menu?
 @{" Commands " Link "Commands"}          AmIRC at your command.
 @{" Configuration " Link "Configuration"}     Customizing your environment.
 @{" ARexx " Link "ARexx"}             Heavy magic.

- Other Stuff: -

 @{" AmIRC Support " Link "AmIRC Support"}     How to get help and updates.
 @{" Index " Link "Index"} 


@EndNode

@Node "About AmIRC" "AmIRC.guide/About AmIRC"
@Next "What's new?"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc "Main"

About AmIRC
***********

In short, AmIRC is the most versatile IRC client for the Amiga
computer. It allows you to chat to other users worldwide over the
internet using IRC.

IRC stands for @{i}Internet Relay Chat@{ui}, originally written by Jarkko
Oikarinen <jto@tolsun.oulu.fi>. In a nutshell, IRC consists of a network
of computers (servers) that are connected to each other via the
internet or a LAN, and allow users with proper client software to
connect and chat with each other. Within this network, virtual space is
divided up into channels, usually with a topic of conversation, where
users can talk in groups.  During your ventures on IRC you will notice
there are a lot of special expressions and abbreviations. Make sure you
have a look at the list of commonly used @{"IRC Terms" Link "IRC Terms"} and expressions in
this guide.

IRC used to be a technical matter with the user having to type in
commands to connect to a network and to send message to a specific
channel.  AmIRC takes care of the technical part with a comfortable
user interface without compromising on flexibility.

Over the last years AmIRC has been constantly improved and updated. The
already long list of @{"Features" Link "Features"} was constantly growing resulting in the
current version 3.5 with the following @{"new features" Link "What's new?"}.


@EndNode

@Node "What's new?" "AmIRC.guide/What's new?"
@Next "Features"
@Prev "About AmIRC"
@Toc "Main"

What's new?
***********

New since last release:
-----------------------

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{"QUERY" Link "QUERY"} command now takes "+", "-" or a "msg" as (optional)
     arguments allowing you to either force it to open in the main
     window or a seperate window, regardless of the default setting or
     to immediately send a message when opening the window.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}Notify@{ub} window now has a @{"QUERY" Link "QUERY"} button to easily open a Query
     window with a notified nick.

   @{b}*@{ub} Both @{b}Nick changes@{ub} and @{b}DCC requests@{ub} can now be diverted to the Info
     Message window.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}Log function@{ub} has been moved from the 'L' button in the channel
     window to the Context or RMB menu on the channel or query button.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}Configuration@{ub} window has been re-arranged and features some
     new options.

Other recently added features:
------------------------------

   @{b}*@{ub} AmIRC now handles @{b}inline channelnames@{ub} which means that if a
     channelname appears in the channel you can now double click it to
     enter the actual channel.

   @{b}*@{ub} AmIRC's @{b}Pages@{ub} mode features "Tabs" at the top of the window
     through which you can access the corresponding channel. Page mode
     also fully suppports drag & drop to attach and detach chats to the
     main window.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{"CLEAR" Link "CLEAR"} command allows you to easily clear any buffer.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{"FAKE" Link "FAKE"} command allows you to fake servermessages that will be
     processed by AmIRC.

   @{b}*@{ub} New @{b}Conference Mode@{ub} will suppress Join and Part messages in the
     channel window.

   @{b}*@{ub} You can now load/unload @{b}Plugins@{ub} from within AmIRC using
     @{"LOAD" Link "LOAD"},@{"RELOAD" Link "RELOAD"} and @{"UNLOAD" Link "UNLOAD"}.

   @{b}*@{ub} If you use a name for a @{b}Log File@{ub} that already exists, AmIRC will
     now ask if you want to "Append" to it or "Overwrite" it.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{"QUERY" Link "QUERY"} command now uniconifies a @{b}Query window@{ub} if it is issued
     with a nick that is attached to an iconified Query window. You can
     disable the Query windows from opening when you are away.

   @{b}*@{ub} The Tray window now has a @{b}Context Menu@{ub} (Right Mouse Button menu)
     through which it can be snapshot, brought to the front or back and
     closed.

   @{b}*@{ub} From Version 3.0 AmIRC needs a @{b}New Keyfile@{ub}! You will need to
     upgrade to be able to use this new version to the fullest.

   @{b}*@{ub} You can now open and close a window by double clicking on its
     button in the @{b}Tray Window@{ub}.

   @{b}*@{ub} AmIRC now supports @{b}Mousewheel@{ub} scrolling.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}Setup window@{ub} is now layout in MUI Prefs style.

   @{b}*@{ub} New @{"RECONNECT" Link "RECONNECT"} command allows easily reconnecting to a server.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added @{b}IRCNet@{ub} commands for @{"Ban exceptions" Link "EXCADD"}and @{"Auto-Invite" Link "INVADD"}.

   @{b}*@{ub} Channel name gadget now has a @{b}Context Menu@{ub} which makes @{"rejoining" Link "CYCLE"} or
     @{"leaving" Link "LEAVE"} a channel only a right mouse button click away.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}Userlist counter@{ub} now shows number of users & channel
     operators. When channel has a user limit it will become a gauge
     showing the channel filling.

   @{b}*@{ub} Channel window and logs now have a (configurable) @{b}timestamp@{ub}.

   @{b}*@{ub} Any @{b}URL@{ub} sent to the channel will now be underlined and clickable,
     giving direct access to them. The URL Grabber will get them too
     for later reference. AmIRC now also recognizes URLs that aren't
     preceded with http:// and FTP URLs.

   @{b}*@{ub} AmIRC will ask for a @{b}Browser@{ub} if none can be found using either
     OpenURL.library, Sendbrowser.amirx or Voyager IPC.

   @{b}*@{ub} AmIRC will now look for the ENV Variables @{b}REALNAME@{ub} and @{b}USER@{ub} upon
     start-up and use those if available.

   @{b}*@{ub} AmIRC now supports @{"ColourCodes" Link "COLOURCODES"}, which means it will show
     individual message colours set by the sender! Rest assured this
     feature can be switched off! :) (Use at own risk ;-)

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}Channel Limit@{ub} and @{b}Keyword@{ub} fields are switched between text and
     string object according to the user's status. i.e. When the user
     is not allowed to change them, he cannot access them.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}Channel Limit@{ub} and @{b}Keyword@{ub} fields are hidden when not the modes
     are not active on a channel.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}Topic@{ub} is now a text field as long as the user is not a
     @{"Channel Operator" Link "OP"} and the channel has @{"Topic Protection" Link "MODE"}, as the user
     is not allowed to change the @{"Topic" Link "TOPIC"} anyway.

   @{b}*@{ub} When MUI Bubble Help is active, the @{"TOPIC" Link "TOPIC"} window now comes up with
     a bubble containing the user who set it and when, as well as the
     complete topic string.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}Text Input Gadgets@{ub} now have a popup menu when the right mouse
     button is pressed when the mouse is on them.

   @{b}*@{ub} With the new @{b}Terminal Login Mode@{ub} AmIRC will open a mini 'telnet'
     connection window after the initial server connection. This allows
     you to bypass any firewalls, use relays etc.  (This mode is
     activated by starting AmIRC from the shell using: "AmIRC
     TerminalMode" or "AmIRC TM").

   @{b}*@{ub} New @{b}Single Channel Window@{ub} mode allows to join multiple channels in
     a single window.


@EndNode

@Node "Features" "AmIRC.guide/Features"
@Next "Requirements"
@Prev "What's new?"
@Toc "Main"

Features
********

   @{b}*@{ub} Runs with Genesis, AmiTCP, Miami and AS225 without additional
     support libraries.

   @{b}*@{ub} Built-in highly optimized @{"DCC" Link "DCC"} drivers for SEND, TSEND and MOVE,
     with asynchronous file I/O and threaded network handling. Supports
     Drag&Drop sending of files and DCC.

   @{b}*@{ub} Transparent implementation of @{"DCC CHAT" Link "DCC"} routing all @{"/MSG" Link "MSG"}s
     automatically via DCC CHAT if applicable, to save runtime and
     reduce IRC load.  Option to automatically accept DCC CHAT
     connections.

   @{b}*@{ub} Ultra fast text output and scrolling. Supports Cut&Paste for the
     list text. Supports proportional fonts.

   @{b}*@{ub} Internal CTCP flood and DCC bomb protection.

   @{b}*@{ub} Full support of the 'Undernet' IRC extensions, both reply codes and
     additional IRC commands.

   @{b}*@{ub} Intuitive channel display with user list and channel mode overview.
     Channel modes can easily be changed via gadgets. Configurable user
     action list to perform whatever action you like on users in channel
     by the press of a mouse button.

   @{b}*@{ub} Supports @{"QUERY" Link "QUERY"} windows for private chat.

   @{b}*@{ub} Supports 'smart' banning.

   @{b}*@{ub} Versatile @{"ARexx" Link "ARexx"} port including server message parsing ("event
     trapping") and commandline/script interaction.

   @{b}*@{ub} Easy command line aliasing.

   @{b}*@{ub} Built-in IdentD (automatically disabled if another IdentD is
     already installed).

   @{b}*@{ub} Supports nick notification, highlighting, ignoring, and kickban.

   @{b}*@{ub} Versatile event handling allows you to bind sound effects,
     auto-deiconify or rexx scripts to certain events.

   @{b}*@{ub} Server phone book.

   @{b}*@{ub} Last nick history stores the nicknames of the last nicks you've
     send MSGs to, received MSGs from or addressed publicly with
     'nick:'.  Reference can be used in all commands which require nick
     names, e.g.  @{"/MSG" Link "MSG"}, @{"/OP" Link "OP"}, @{"/DEOP" Link "DEOP"}. Automatic nick expansion on public
     messages with ':'.

   @{b}*@{ub} TAB messaging to automatically cycle the list of last used
     nicknames with a @{"/MSG" Link "MSG"} prefix.

   @{b}*@{ub} Auto rejoin channel on @{"/KICK" Link "KICK"} and auto reconnect to server facility.

   @{b}*@{ub} Auto @{"/AWAY" Link "AWAY"} after a user-specified idle time-out. Also, auto unaway
     after sending public and/or private msgs.

   @{b}*@{ub} Auto update download.  Check for and download new releases with a
     simple click.

   @{b}*@{ub} URL grabber for interfacing with a web browser. (Using
     OpenURL.library or @{"ARexx" Link "ARexx"})

   @{b}*@{ub} Support for DALnet extensions.

   @{b}*@{ub} AmIRC is fully @{b}localized@{ub} thanks to ATO (http://ato.vapor.com/ato).


@EndNode

