@Node "RX_GETCHANNEL" "AmIRC.guide/RX_GETCHANNEL"
@Next "RX_GETSELECTEDUSER"
@Prev "RX_GETDCC"
@Toc "ARexx"

GETCHANNEL
==========

Usage:
     GETCHANNEL WINNUM/N

DESCRIPTION:

Returns the name of the channel currently active in the format:
"#channel."

If the WINNUM argument is given , the channel for that window is
returned.

EXAMPLES:

     options results;"getchannel";"ECHO" result

     options results;"getchannel WINNUM=1";"ECHO" result

RELATED TOPICS: See @{"RX_CHANNELS" Link "RX_CHANNELS"}, @{"RX_GETWINNUM" Link "RX_GETWINNUM"}.


@EndNode

@Node "RX_CHANNELS" "AmIRC.guide/RX_CHANNELS"
@Next "RX_GETDCC"
